      "name": "05 - Fault Tolerance",
      "description": "Tests for circuit breakers, rate limiting, and service isolation. Each request includes manual steps in its description that must be completed before sending.",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "[CB] Place Order — Customer Service Down",
          "description": "**Before running:**\n```\ndocker stop food-delivery-customer-service\n```\n\n**Expected:** HTTP 503 from CustomerClient fallback. After 5 failures within 10 calls, the circuit opens and subsequent calls return 503 immediately with 'circuit breaker open' in the body.\n\n**Restore:**\n```\ndocker start food-delivery-customer-service\n```\nCircuit auto-transitions to HALF_OPEN after 5 s, then CLOSED after 3 successful probes.",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Returns 503 when Customer Service is down', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([503, 201]);",
                  "});",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 503) {",
                  "  const b = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('Error message present', () => pm.expect(b.error || b.message).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "}"
